TPU TYRE DESIGN


TREAD DESIGN:
Chevron/ V-lugs —> best for ramps + uneven terrains
Unidirectional treads 
Abrasion-resistant so that the tyre's material does not scrape off 


Recommended Dimensions assuming the wheel diameter is 30cm
Angle: 30-45 degrees
Lug height: 8–12 mm
Lug thickness: ≥6 mm
Lug spacing: 1.2–1.5 × lug width
Rounded edges (fillet radius ≥2 mm)





TPU shore should be around 85-90A (balance between soft and hard). Good for a 50kg UGV




HUB DESIGN:
Rigid hub with proper locking method. 
Material - Aluminium or nylon CF for robust attachment of the motor, so that it can handle the torque




SPOKES DESIGN:


          RADIAL SPOKES                                       GYROID SPOKES

These infill patterns will help in shock absorption
Radial pattern is considered best for heavy UGVs
Void ratio should be 35-50%


